<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 91 / Appointments: Restructure at Inchcape
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
INCHCAPE is re-organising its worldwide operations on a business stream
basis. The following board changes will be made, effective from January 1,
1992. Mr Alan Marsh, chairman of Toyota (GB), will be appointed a main board
director and will manage all Toyota businesses worldwide. Mr Derek
Whittaker, director in charge of the group's European motors operations,
will become a main board director and responsible for all worldwide motor
operations other than Toyota. Mr David John, a main board director, will
become responsible for the worldwide marketing and distribution business
stream.
Mr Jean-Paul Parayre has been appointed a non-executive director. He is vice
chairman and executive vice president of Group Lyonnaise des Eaux-Dumez, and
chairman of Trans-Manche Construction. He is on the boards of Alcatel
Alsthom, and of Alfred McAlpine, and on the supervisory board of Peugeot.
*****
PERSIMMON, York, has appointed Mr Michael Walker as construction director of
Persimmon Homes (East Midlands). Mr Steve Feneley has been appointed
managing director of Persimmon Homes (North Midlands).
*****
IVERNIA WEST has appointed to the board Mr Michael Gordon, vice president,
corporate finance, Minorco, and Mr Christian Schaffalitzky, managing
director of Crowe Schaffalitzky and Associates. Mr Andrew Woollett has
resigned from the board to pursue other mining interests.
*****
MIDLANDS ELECTRICITY has appointed Mr Clive Parsons as human resources
director from June 1. He is personnel director of British Gypsum.
*****
COOPERS &amp; LYBRAND DELOITTE has appointed Mr David Anton as
partner-in-charge, national litigation support unit.
*****
Mr Peter Kempster has been appointed head of the tax and trusts department
at NABARRO NATHANSON, taking over from Mr Ron Gulliver who is retiring but
remains a consultant.
*****
TYNE TEES TELEVISION, independent television contractor for north east
England, has appointed Mr Adrian Metcalfe as its director of programmes and
Mr James Lancaster as director of resources. Mr Metcalfe joins Tyne Tees
after a career at Channel 4 and Sky TV, and Mr Lancaster joins from ITN.
*****
STREETS COMMUNICATIONS has appointed Mr Alex Glover to the board. He was
with Valin Pollen.
*****
CAMERON MARKBY HEWITT, City solicitors, has appointed aviation specialist Mr
Tim Brymer as a partner. He joins from Brymer Marland &amp; Co. Ms Julia
Onslow-Cole, Ms Fiona O'Neill and Mr Stephen Foster have been promoted to
partners.
*****
Mr J. Stanley Mowatt has been appointed a non-executive director of the
SETON HEALTHCARE GROUP. He was chairman and chief executive of Ultra
Laboratories, recently acquired by Seton. He is chairman and majority
shareholder of the Radwinter Group, and will continue as a director of
Ultra.
*****
Mr Brian Waghorn has been elected senior partner of SCRUTTON BLAND, Ipswich
accountants, and Mr David Foster has been elected to the new post of
managing partner. Mr Waghorn succeeds Mr Geoffrey Lockhart who retires but
becomes a part-time consultant. Mr Andrew Strickland has joined as a partner
in the Colchester office. He was with Grant Thornton. Mr David Verney has
become a partner at Ipswich.
</TEXT>
