FT  03 MAY 91 / Relief operation begins for Bangladesh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BANGLADESH was pledged millions of dollars in aid from foreign governments
and relief organisations yesterday to help victims of the cyclone which
struck the country on Monday.
The resort district of Cox's Bazar (pictured) is just one of the areas in
ruins and still under flood waters. The death-toll has risen to 37,000 and
could climb to more than 100,000, relief officials in Dhaka said. At least
20,000 people are still missing and more than 10m people have lost their
homes.
Britain has pledged immediate aid of Pounds 2.5m and the European Community
will give Ecu 10m (Pounds 7m).
