<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 91 / Appointments: Barclays recruits Japanese and Dutch directors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Banking Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BARCLAYS has appointed its first two non-British directors. They are Mr
Shijuro Ogata of Japan and Mr Jan Peelen of the Netherlands, writes David
Lascelles, Banking Editor.
Mr Ogata was deputy governor for international relations at the Bank of
Japan and subsequently deputy governor of the Japan Development Bank, from
which he retired earlier this year. Mr Peelen is a director of Unilever with
responsibility for the East Asian and Pacific region.
Sir John Quinton, Barclays' chairman, said the appointments would be of
value to Barclays as an international corporate and investment bank, and he
hoped eventually to appoint a director from the US as well.
Mr Ogata said he hoped his appointment would lead to greater international
understanding on banking issues at a time when global banking markets were
becoming increasingly integrated.
Observer, page 16
*****
Mr Charlie Middleton has been appointed chief executive of THE ROYAL BANK OF
SCOTLAND (NASSAU), succeeding Mr Reno Brown, chairman and chief executive,
who retires on May 31.
