<DOCNO>FT911-1722</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-BECBBACSFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>910503
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 91 / World Commodites Prices: Fruit and Vegetables
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Avocado at 35-50p each (60-90p) is the best fruit buy this week, along with
French Golden Delicious apples at 40-55p a lb (40-55p) and grapes from Cape
and Chile at 75p-Pounds 1.25p a lb (75p-Pounds 1.25p). Kiwifruit at 15-20p
each (15-20p), plums at 75p-Pounds 1.20 a lb, and oranges at 5-28p (5-28p)
are all excellent fruit choices. Cauliflower at 45-65p (55-70p) is a good
vegetable buy, and mushrooms at 60p-Pounds 1.10 a  1/2 lb are plentiful.
Cucumbers are good value this week at 55-70p each (55-70p), together with
tomatoes at 65-90p a lb (65-90p) and Iceberg lettuce at 60-85p each
(60-85p).
