FT  03 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Losses at BDA rise 40% to Pounds 2.17m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BDA Holdings saw losses increase further in the year to January 31 1991 due
to its decision to reduce finished residential property prices to revive
sales momentum.
On sales up 15 per cent at Pounds 7.02m (Pounds 6.08m) the pre-tax loss
increased by 40 per cent from Pounds 1.55m to Pounds 2.17m. Directors of
this south-east-based housebuilder said yesterday that in view of the
continuing uncertain outlook no dividend would be paid. The last
distribution was for 1989.
Directors also reviewed the value of the property portfolio and in addition
to the Pounds 855,000 write-down taken at the time of the rights issue in
August, a further Pounds 190,000 has been provided.
The decision to reduce prices meant that at the year end more than three
quarters of the finished residential stock had been sold and debt reduced to
Pounds 1.15m (Pounds 7.47m). Losses per share came through at 14.6p (11.1p).
