L Noel &amp; Sons, a maker and distributor of herbs, spices, cocktail cherries
and other fine foods formerly part of Fitch Lovell, for Pounds 8.5m cash. BT
has acquired the 55 per cent of Westminster Cable Company it did not own.
*****
ESSEX WATER has posted a circular to shareholders detailing proposals to
convert status from a statutory water company to a public limited company.
On conversion, voting and non-voting irredeemable stock would be converted
into voting and non-voting ordinary shares, no longer subject to dividend
limits. The present 8.625 per cent redeemable preference stock 1993 will be
converted into 9.625 per cent redeemable preference shares 1993, holding
cumulative dividend rights and preferential rights on a winding up.
