<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Aberforth Split Level for market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ABERFORTH SPLIT Level Trust (Aslet) is joining the stock market via a
placing and intermediaries offer which will raise Pounds 28.9m after
expenses.
This is the first new issue to use the combination of a placing and
intermediaries offer. James Capel, the trust's sponsor, advertised the
availability of the shares to intermediaries via the Stock Exchange. As a
result, 35 per cent of the offer is being sold via intermediaries, mainly
private client stockbrokers.
The trust, which is managed by Aberforth Partners, will concentrate on
smaller company investments. Up to 15m income and 15m capital shares are
being issued at 100p each.
Income shareholders are entitled to all the income of the company - a
prospective gross dividend yield of 12 per cent - and a repayment of 10p per
share (the par value) if the trust is wound up. Capital shareholders do not
receive any income but are entitled to all the assets after the income
shareholders are repaid.
Aberforth established another smaller companies trust last year called
Ascot, the shares of which have consistently traded at a premium to its net
asset value. Dealings in the new trust's shares are expected to start on May
14.
</TEXT>
